<p> Next Article: Man jailed for using pitbull as a weapon </p>
<p> Man burnt after cigarette ignites methylated spirit fumes </p>
<p> 5:19 PM Tuesday Jan 17, 2012 </p>
<p> Tweet </p>
<p> Email </p>
<p> Print </p>
<p> Expand </p>
<p> File photo / Thinkstock </p>
<p> A Gisborne man is in hospital with moderate burns after a cigarette ignited fumes from an open can of methylated spirits. </p>
<p> The 26-year-old was working in a shed at the back of his property in the suburb of Kaiti earlier this afternoon. </p>
<p> He suffered burns to his right leg and arm. </p>
<p> The Fire Service says the cigarette lit a shade cloth and a couch in the shed. </p>
<p> They say it shows just how important it is to take care when lighting cigarettes around flammable liquids. </p>
<p> - Newstalk ZB </p>
<p> Smoker burned filling mower </p>
